== Description ==

The '''Arch StructuralSystem''' tool creates a structural system from a [[Arch_Structure|Structure]] object and one or two [[Arch_Axis|Axis]] objects. It distributes the structure along the axes, creating repetitive structures like column or beam grids.

== Usage ==

# Select an [[Arch_Structure|Arch Structure]] object.
# Select one or two [[Arch_Axis|Arch Axis]] objects to define the grid. If two Axis objects are selected, one or more of their axes must intersect.
# Select the {{MenuCommand|Utils → Structure Tools → [[Image:Arch_StructuralSystem.svg|16px]] Structural System}} option from the menu.
# The structural system is created.

== Notes ==

* The resulting structural system maintains a relationship with the Axis object(s).
* For a single Axis object the start point of each axis line will host a copy of the Structure object. For two Axis objects each axis intersection will host a copy.
* The position of the original Structure object relative to the origin is taken into account.


